<li id="cite_note-73"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-73">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Hamill, Denis. <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/movies/hamill-actor-danny-aiello-tells-memoir-article-1.2012485">"Hamill: Danny Aiello tells it like it is in memoir <i>I Only Know Who I Am When I Am Somebody Else</i>"</a>, <i><a href="/wiki/New_York_Daily_News" title="New York Daily News">New York Daily News</a></i>, November 15, 2014. Accessed September 27, 2018. "The actor did a lot of running from the police growing up in Manhattan's West Side and the South Bronx, making money shining shoes, running numbers, shooting pool and even robbing safes."</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-74"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-74">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://newyork.cbslocal.com/2015/02/09/listen-nate-archibald-talks-nbas-history-of-nyc-basketball-map/">"Watch: Nate Archibald Talks NBA’s 'History Of NYC Basketball' Map"</a>, <a href="/wiki/WCBS-TV" title="WCBS-TV">WCBS-TV</a>, February 9, 2015. Accessed September 27, 2018. "Archibald, nicknamed 'Tiny,' is very much a part of New York’s illustrious basketball history. The six-time NBA All-Star grew up in the South Bronx and attended DeWitt Clinton High School."</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-75"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-75">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://abc7ny.com/archive/7227176/">"Bronx natives Aventura set to rock sold-out MSG"</a>, <a href="/wiki/WABC-TV" title="WABC-TV">WABC-TV</a>, January 20, 2010. Accessed September 27, 2018. "Aventura was raised in the South Bronx. They formed their group in 1996. Now, they say they can't even walk the streets without fans hounding them."</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-76"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-76">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Laurence, Rebecca. <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.bbc.com/culture/story/20130809-the-party-where-hip-hop-was-born">"40 years on from the party where hip hop was born"</a>, <a href="/wiki/BBC" title="BBC">BBC</a>, October 21, 2014. Accessed September 27, 2018. "But by 1977, his star had waned and other rival New York DJs, notably the South Bronx’s Afrika Bambaataa and Grandmaster Flash were waiting in the wings."</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-77"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-77">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Estevez, Marjua. <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.vibe.com/featured/interview-swizz-beatz-piano-district-no-commission/">"How Swizz Beatz Halted 'Piano District' Invention With South Bronx Art Fair"</a>, <i><a href="/wiki/Vibe_(magazine)" title="Vibe (magazine)">Vibe (magazine)</a></i>, August 17, 2016. Accessed September 27, 2018. "The pleasant surprise of Celia Cruz’s dulcet vocals echoing throughout a maze of brightly decorated corridors—a hodgepodge of 2D, 3D and cinematographic works—instantaneously brought to mind Swizz Beatz’s little-talked about Puerto Rican ancestry.... No surprise there, considering the DJ-turned-record producer spent much of his childhood raised by his mother in the South Bronx projects, 12 blocks from where the fair was standing."</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-78"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-78">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://daily.redbullmusicacademy.com/2016/05/jellybean-benitez-remembers-nyc-clubs-of-yesteryear">"Jellybean Benitez Remembers NYC Clubs of Yesteryear"</a>, <a href="/wiki/Red_Bull_Music_Academy" title="Red Bull Music Academy">Red Bull Music Academy</a>. Accessed September 27, 2018. "A giant of New York City club culture during the 1980s, John 'Jellybean' Benitez was born to a Puerto Rican mother in the South Bronx."</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-79"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-79">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=Ed9m2dydpwUC&amp;pg=PA32&amp;lpg=PA32&amp;dq=hank+greenberg+%22the+bronx%22+neighborhood&amp;source=bl&amp;ots=dedk1rROXq&amp;sig=PzvqGm8Tg6Qk1Yr4_S8aaaeUvdA&amp;hl=en&amp;sa=X&amp;ved=0ahUKEwiIoYCOrZjaAhUId98KHY20Dm4Q6AEIbTAO#v=onepage&amp;q=hank%20greenberg%20%22the%20bronx%22%20neighborhood&amp;f=false">Hank Greenberg: The Hero Who Didn't Want to Be One - Mark Kurlansky - Google Books</a></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-80"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-80">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite class="citation web"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://brie.hunter.cuny.edu/hpe/2010/05/16/fox-street-co-op-draws-middle-income-residents-2/">"Fox Street co-op draws middle income residents"</a>. Hunts Point Express<span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">10 October</span> 2015</span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Fox+Street+co-op+draws+middle+income+residents&amp;rft.pub=Hunts+Point+Express&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fbrie.hunter.cuny.edu%2Fhpe%2F2010%2F05%2F16%2Ffox-street-co-op-draws-middle-income-residents-2%2F&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ASouth+Bronx" class="Z3988"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r879151008"/></span>
